    "Smith, J. M. Powis (John Merlin, St. Jerome": "Origen mentions a Gospel of the Twelve in Hom. 1 in Lk. In Contr. Pelag.\n3.1.2, Jerome seems to identify this gospel with both the Gospel according to the\nHebrews and the gospel used by the Nazarenes. He writes: \u201cIn the Gospel accord-\ning to the Hebrews, which is written in the Chaldee and Syrian language, but in\nHebrew characters, and is used by the Nazarenes to this day (I mean the Gospel\naccording to the Apostles or, as is generally maintained, the Gospel according\nto Matthew, a copy of which is in the library at Caesarea) .....\u201d NPNF2, 6.",
